cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about improving the performance of a neural network architecture for pose estimation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new module for integrating global context, which involves modifying the network architecture, suggesting that it could also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper reports on the speed of the network, which could be relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
